parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The degradation of the wiring harness insulation can cause electrical system failures, leading to potential safety hazards, such as fires, and can also result in costly repairs.
The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to failure of airbag deployment in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag light on the dashboard remains illuminated
the airbag system fails to deploy in the event of an accident
the airbag system is temporarily repaired but the problem persists.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected lurching or rocking of the vehicle after parking can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially if the vehicle is on an incline or has occupants or nearby pedestrians.
symptoms: The vehicle lurches forward or rocks backward after parking and turning off the ignition
the vehicle slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations
the vehicle has difficulty shifting into gear.
